<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05020g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05020g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05020g"> 20(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> crurifragium</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When the bodies of the unfortunate trio were taken down from the cross, the legs of the two thieves were broken, but the soldiers passed by Jesus, deeming him already dead. This process, known as the <mark>Crurifragium</mark>, was a distinct punishment from crucifixion. It consisted of breaking, with hammers or clubs, the bones from the hips to the feet. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Crucifixion] 202</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
